  "texts": [
    "The various programs that allow for the creation of ATR material have options to export the generated and/or corrected transcriptions.",
    "When possible, both the transcriptions and images should be exported, depending on any potential copyright or image rights.",
    "4 If this is not possible, it is helpful to at minimum sustainably store the \"pure\" transcriptions.",
    "Within the Transkribus tool, provided by the READ-COOP SCE, the export appears as shown in 1.",
    "5 Widely used standards, like ALTO XML, PAGE XML, and hOCR allow for an align-ment between image and transcription -based on coordinates -which is required to connect transcribed text on a character, word or line basis with images and allows for the opportunity to (re)train models based on machine learning."
